rical experience in this space includes investments in hospitals pharmaceuticals medical products manufacturers distributors and service providers  our extensive experience across the healthcare value chain allows us to better and more rapidly understand and support our management teams in the face of the key trends affecting the sector related team current portfolio case studies back waters regions industry healthcare year  bain capital acquired waters a manufacturer of liquid chromatography instruments for the pharmaceutical and life science industries in  an industry leader with a large installed instrument base broad product suite and strong global presence bain capital saw an opportunity to partner with management to improve the waters’ performance and drive continued global expansion opportunities bain capital partnered with management to carve out waters as a standalone entity from milipore corporation investing in research and development and the acquisition of acquired phase separations limited to complement waters’ existing consumable product portfolio following continued product development and performance improvement in the united states and abroad including an  increase in sales and an  increase in earnings during the first year of ownership the company went public in  case studies are not intended to be illustrative for investment purposes and should not be relied upon for investment decision making this should not be considered an offer or solicitation of securities or investment services information is for informational purposes only and intended for management teams considering partnering with bain capital partners bain capital bain capital investor portal please log in to access your account information if you have any questions regarding your account please contact email protected sign on to your account select an account private equity credit public equity ventures double impact life sciences questions call us  x  global phone support email us em